23 PART IV. EXTEND THE RETENTION PERIOD FOR CLOSED COMPLAINTS TO
24 ALLOW FOR REVIEW BY THE PROSECUTOR
25 SECTION 4. G.S. 7B-1703(c) reads as rewritten:
26 "(c) If the juvenile court counselor determines that a petition should not be filed or the
27 complaint handled as a juvenile consultation, the juvenile court counselor shall notify the
28 complainant and the victim, if the complainant is not the victim, immediately in writing with
29 specific reasons for the decision, whether or not legal sufficiency was found, and whether the
30 matter was closed or diverted and retained, and shall include notice of the complainant's and
31 victim's right to have the decision reviewed by the prosecutor. The juvenile court counselor shall
32 sign the complaint after indicating on it:
33 (1) The date of the determination;
34 (2) The words "Not Approved for Filing"; and
35 (3) Whether the matter is "Closed" or "Diverted and Retained".
36 Except as provided in G.S. 7B-1706, any complaint not approved for filing as a juvenile
37 petition or handled as a juvenile consultation shall be destroyed by the juvenile court counselor
38 after holding the complaint for a temporary period of at least one year to allow review as provided
39 in G.S. 7B-1704 and G.S. 7B-1705."
