41 PART V. CREATE A CRIMINAL OFFENSE FOR ESCAPING FROM A JUVENILE
42 JUSTICE FACILITY OR OFFICER
43 SECTION 5. Article 33 of Chapter 14 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
44 a new section to read:
45 "§ 14-256.2. Escape from juvenile detention facilities or officers.
46 (a) Offense and Punishment. – If any person shall break any detention facility, holdover
47 facility, or youth development center, being lawfully detained therein, or shall escape from the
48 lawful custody of any employee, guard, or officer of the Division of Juvenile Justice of the
49 Department of Public Safety, the person is guilty of a Class 1 misdemeanor, except that the person
50 is guilty of a Class H felony if any of the following apply:
Page 4 House Bill 483-Second Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) The person has been charged with a felony and has been committed to the
2 facility pending trial or transfer to the State prison system.
3 (2) The person is alleged to be within the jurisdiction of the juvenile court for an
4 offense that would be a felony if committed by an adult and has been placed
5 in secure custody.
6 (3) The person has been adjudicated delinquent for an offense that would be a
7 felony if committed by an adult and has been placed in secure custody or
8 committed to the custody of the Division of Juvenile Justice and Delinquency
9 Prevention for placement in a youth development center.
10 (b) Definitions. – For purposes of this section, the terms "detention facility," "holdover
11 facility," and "youth development center" are as defined in G.S. 7B-1501."
